                  <persName id="t18290219-35-person394">
                  JOSEPH 
                  WESTON
               <interp inst="t18290219-35-person394" type="surname" value="WESTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290219-35-person394" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290219-35-person394" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18290219-35-viclabel193" type="occupation">clerk</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290219-35-victim391 t18290219-35-viclabel193"></join> at Torrington's wharf, Battle-bridge. The prisoner was nurse to my late wife - when she died, I ordered a suit of mourning; the prisoner continued there: on the 15th, my suit of mourning was brought to the counting-house - I had not worn it at all.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290219-35-person395">
                  FRANCIS 
                  PARKER
               <interp inst="t18290219-35-person395" type="surname" value="PARKER"></interp>
